<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612330>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Cotesia ferruginea. A—habitus, lateral; B—wings and partial details of metasoma; C—head (partially), mesosoma and first tergite, dorsal; D—propodeum and metasoma, dorsal; E—head frontal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612330/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612326>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Cotesia testacea female holotype (A, C–G) and male paratype (B). A and B—habitus, lateral; C—wings; Dhead, frontal; E—head, dorsal; F—propodeum and metasoma, dorsal; G—head and mesosoma (partially), dorsal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612326/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612328>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Cotesia testacea female paratype. A—habitus, lateral; B—head, fronto-ventral; C—head, frontal; D—wings; Epropodeum and metasoma, dorsal; F—head and mesosoma, dorsal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612328/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2612332>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Distribution map of Cotesia testacea in Japan and Korea. The red circles show species distribution based on examined specimens (or revised literature); the yellow circle denotes likely distribution (based on literature) that could not be checked for this paper." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2612332/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

